# AI-Powered PDF Learning Assistant for Students (Python RAG Stack)

Design and develop a production-ready, modular monolith backend and a modern frontend for the AI-powered PDF Learning Assistant. This stack uses **Python + FastAPI**, **MySQL** for relational metadata, **Qdrant** (local storage) for Vector Search, and **React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS** for the user interface.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Python installation**: We will configure a project-specific virtual environment. If Python is not installed globally or registered in your system PATH, we recommend installing Python 3.12 via `winget install Python.Python.3.12` or python.org.
> - **MySQL credentials**: The application will expect MySQL server details. We will configure these in a root `.env` file (Database: `pdf_assistant_db`, User: `root`, password: default or configurable).
> - **Gemini API Key**: A `GEMINI_API_KEY` is required. It can be provided in the backend `.env` file or dynamically entered via the frontend settings screen.

